              Abstract  Proposal number: 	0114854 PI: 	Anne Cunningham	 Institution: 	UC
              Berkeley Title: 	Teachers' Disciplinary Knowledge of Reading and its
              Relationship to K-3 Pedagogy and Student Achievement    This is a planning
              grant for a project that will investigate the current level of K-3 elementary
              school teachers.  disciplinary knowledge, beliefs, and knowledge calibration in
              reading processes, development, and pedagogy. The project will use a set of
              workshops and development activities in the planning of how to conduct a series
              of experimental,  longitudinal, and qualitative studies that will lead to a
              greater understanding of the type and depth of knowledge needed to be an
              effective teacher of reading (as evidenced by student performance) and the
              models of professional development that facilitate the growth  of teachers.
              disciplinary knowledge, beliefs, and pedagogy in reading and literacy.     
